{
  "texts": [
    "The corresponding graphene-scale Kekulé patterns can be detected by spin-unpolarized or spin-polarized STM, respectively, and by phase coherently comparing STM measurements in nearby moiré unit cells one can also detect the incommensurate modulation that is the hallmark of IKS.",
    "Pioneering experiments have detected Kekulé charge order near ν = 2 in both MA-TBG [25] and its close cousin, twisted symmetric trilayer graphene [26] with a q IVC consistent with both detailed HF energetics and the \"lobe principle\".",
    "We now briefly discuss the structure of the IKS states at |ν| = 1, 2.",
    "At ν = -2, we can construct a 'spin singlet' IKS state by simply creating ν = -3 IKS states for each spin species separately.",
    "Specifically, we haveP-2 (k, k ′) = 1 4 (1 + n ⊥ k • γ)(1 + m k • η)δ k,k ′."
  ]
}